an class='sdata'>ājñām</span>) to submit to, obey, &nbsp;<span class='ls'>ib.</span>&nbsp;; <div style='margin-top:0.6em;'></div></div> (with <span class='sdata'>ūrjām</span>) to exert, employ, &nbsp;<span class='ls'>Bhaṭṭ.</span>&nbsp; : <div style='margin-top:0.6em;'></div></div><strong><span>Pass.</span></strong> <span class='sdata'>bhriyate</span> (<span>ep.</span> also <span class='sdata'>˚ti</span>; <span>aor.</span> <span class='sdata'>abhāri</span>), <div style='margin-top:0.6em;'></div></div>to be borne &c., &nbsp;<span class='ls'>RV.</span>&nbsp; &c. &c.: <div style='margin-top:0.6em;'></div></div><strong><span>Caus.</span></strong> <span class='sdata'>bhārayati</span> (<span>aor.</span> <span class='sdata'>abībharat</span>), to cause to bear &c.; <div style='margin-top:0.6em;'></div></div>to engage for hire, &nbsp;<span class='ls'>MBh.</span>&nbsp; : <div style='margin-top:0.6em;'></div></div><strong><span>Desid.</span></strong> <span class='sdata'>bubhūrṣati</span> (&nbsp;<span class='ls'>ŚBr.</span>&nbsp;; &nbsp;<span class='ls'>MārkP.</span>&nbsp;), <span class='sdata'>bibhariṣati</span> (&nbsp;<span class='ls'>Pāṇ. vii, 2, 49</span>&nbsp;), to wish to bear or support or maintain: <div style='margin-top:0.6em;'></div></div><strong><span>Intens.</span></strong> <span class='sdata'>baribharti</span> (3. <span>pl.</span> <span class='sdata'>˚bhrati</span>, &nbsp;<span class='ls'>RV.</span>&nbsp;, where also 2. <span>du.</span> <span class='sdata'>jarbhṛtaḥ</span>), <span class='sdata'>barībharti</span> (&nbsp;<span class='ls'>Kāv.</span>&nbsp;), to bear repeatedly or continually, carry hither and thither.","evidence":{"band":2,"band_label":"frequent -- learn early","rank_all":525,"count_all":1312,"first_era":"Vedic","genre":null,"example":{"sa":"bibhrataḥ","ru":"неся","work":"01_atharvaveda","passage":"1.1","kind":"translation","source":"corpus_lexicon.jsonl (pwg_ru Phase 4, SanskritLexicography/RussianTranslation)"},"badges":[{"field":"band","value":2,"l