-top:0.6em;'></div></div> 1 3 <span>U.</span> (<span class='sdata'>bharati-te; bibharti, bibhṛte</span>, <span class='sdata'>babhāra babhre, bibharāṃcakāra-cakre, abhārṣīṃt-abhṛta</span>, <span class='sdata'>bhariṣyati-te, bhartuṃ, bhṛta</span>; <i><span>pass.</span></i> <span class='sdata'>bhriyate</span>; <i><span>desid.</span></i> <span class='sdata'>bibhariṣati-te</span> or <span class='sdata'>bubhūrṣati-te</span>) <div style='margin-top:0.6em;'></div></div><strong>1</strong> To fill; <span class='sdata'>jaṭharaṃ</span> <span class='sdata'>ko na bibharti kevalaṃ</span> &nbsp;<span class='ls'>Pt. 1. 22.</span>&nbsp; <div style='margin-top:0.6em;'></div></div><strong>2</strong> To fill, pervade, fill with; <span class='sdata'>abhārṣīdadhvaninā</span> <br/>(<span title='Page 0824-a' style='border-bottom: 1px dotted #000; text-decoration: none;'>pb</span>) <span class='sdata'>lokān</span> &nbsp;<span class='ls'>Bk. 15. 24.</span>&nbsp; <div style='margin-top:0.6em;'></div></div><strong>3</strong> To bear, support, uphold, bear up; <span class='sdata'>dhuraṃ dharitryā</span> <span class='sdata'>bibharāṃbabhūva</span> &nbsp;<span class='ls'>R. 18. 45</span>&nbsp;; <span class='sdata'>kūrmo bibharti</span> <span class='sdata'>dharaṇīṃ khalu pṛṣṭhakena</span> &nbsp;<span class='ls'>Ch. P. 50</span>&nbsp;; &nbsp;<span class='ls'>Bk. 17. 16</span>&nbsp; <div style='margin-top:0.6em;'></div></div><strong>4</strong> To maintain, foster, cherish, protect, take care of, nourish; <span class='sdata'>daridrān</span> <span class='sdata'>bhara kauṃteya mā prayaccheśvare dhanaṃ</span> &nbsp;<span class='ls'>H. 1. 15.</span>&nbsp; <div style='margin-top:0.6em;'></div></div><strong>5</strong> To bear, have, possess; <span class='sdata'>siṃdhorbabhāra salilaṃ śayanīyalakṣmīṃ</span> &nbsp;<span class='ls'>Ki. 8. 57</span>&nbsp;; <span class='sdata'>piśunajanaṃ khalu bibhrati kṣitīṃdrāḥ</span> &nbsp;<span class='ls'>Bv. 1. 74</span>&nbsp;; <span class='sdata'>balitrayaṃ cāru babhāra bālā</span> &nbsp;<span class='ls'>Ku. 1. 39</span>&nbsp;; <span class='sdata'>iṃdordainyaṃ tvadatusaraṇakliṣṭakāṃterbibharti</span> &nbsp;<span class='ls'>Me. 84</span>&nbsp;; &nbsp;<span class='ls'>Ś. 2. 4.</span>&nbsp; <div style='margin-top:0.6em;'></div></div><strong>6</strong> To wear; <span class='sdata'>bibhrajjaṭāmaṃḍalaṃ</span> &nbsp;<span class='ls'>Ś. 7. 11</span>&nbsp;; <span class='ls' title='Ś.'>6. 5</span>&nbsp;; <span class='sdata'>vivāhakautukaṃ</span> <span class='sdata'>lalitaṃ bibhrata eva (tasya)</span> &nbsp;<span class='ls'>R. 8. 1</span>&nbsp;, <span class='ls' title='R.'>10. 10</span>&nbsp;; <span class='sdata'>jaṭāśca bibhṛyānnityaṃ</span> &nbsp;<span class='ls'>Ms. 6. 6.</span>&nbsp; <div style='margin-top:0.6em;'></div></div><strong>7</strong> To feel, experience, suffer, endure (joy, sorrow &c.); <span class='sdata'>bhāvaśuddhisahitairmudaṃ jano nāṭakairiva babhāra bhojanaiḥ</span> &nbsp;<span class='ls'>Śi. 14. 50</span>&nbsp;; <span class='sdata'>saṃtrāsamabibhaḥ śakraḥ</span> &nbsp;<span class='ls'>Bk. 17. 108</span>&nbsp;; &nbsp;<span class='ls'>Ś. 7. 21.</span>&nbsp; <div style='margin-top:0.6em;'></div></div><strong>8</strong> To confer, bestow, give, produce; <span class='sdata'>yauvane sadalaṃkārāḥ śobhāṃ</span> <span class='sdata'>bibhrati subhruvaḥ</span> &nbsp;<span class='ls'>Subhāṣ.</span>&nbsp; <div style='margin-top:0.6em;'></div></div><strong>9</strong> To keep, hold, retain (as in memory). <div style='margin-top:0.6em;'></div></div><strong>10</strong> To hire; &nbsp;<span class='ls'>Ms. 11. 62</span>&nbsp;; &nbsp;<span class='ls'>Y. 3. 235.</span>&nbsp; <div style='margin-top:0.6em;'></div></div><strong>11</strong> To bring or carry. <div style='margin-top:0.6em;'></div></div><strong>12</strong> To take away, transport. <div style='margin-top:0.6em;'></div></div><strong>13</strong> <span>Ved.</span> To acquire, gain. (<span class='sdata'>garbhaṃ bhṛ</span> to become pregnant, conceive; <span class='sdata'>kṣitiṃ bhṛ</span> to rule the earth; <span class='sdata'>jaṭāṃ bhṛ</span> to wear matted hair &c.).","evidence":{"band":2,"band_label":"frequent -- learn early","rank_all":525,"count_all":1312,"first_era":"Vedic","genre":null,"example":{"sa":"bibhrataḥ","ru":"неся","work":"01_atharvaveda","passage":"1.1","kind":"translation","source":"corpus_lexicon.jsonl (pwg_ru Phase 4, SanskritLexicography/RussianTranslation)"},"badges":[{"field":"band","value":2,"label":"frequent -- learn early","source":"kosha frequency layer, rank_all (DCS archive.sqlite M9 via VisualDCS)"},{"field":"count_all","value":1312,"label":"1312 attestations in DCS","source":"DCS archive.sqlite M9 (VisualDCS)"},{"field":"first_era","value":"Vedic","label":"first attested: Vedic","source":"DCS archive.sqlite M9 (VisualDCS)"},{"field":"genre","value":null,"label":"genre sketch not derivable from current DCS extraction (only a chronological period vector is stored, no per-genre breakdown)","source":"n/a -- gap documented, not fabricated (see app/evidence.py)"}]}}]}